Not very much, I was a student. And we - of course we attended all the lectures on home nursing, but it - all it meant was - there was a waiting room at one of the stations, we used to man for the troops going through. A
nd - not often really were we called on. And I remember meeting a train of wounded in - late at night you know with feeding cups for men on stretchers.
